The Alex Jones Show
Sunday, 14 July 2013


[sebaygo1]

Show description from theweb site :: On this important Sunday, April 14 edition of the Alex Jones Show, Alex covers the acquittal of George Zimmerman in the Trayvon Martin murder case. The case was highly charged politically and exploited by the establishment as it maneuvers to disarm the American people and make self-defense illegal in the United States like it is in many other parts of the world. Alex covers the possibility of riots in the streets in response to the verdict after weeks of incessant propaganda weighted against Zimmerman and his defense. Jones looks at the likely political ramifications of the trial as the NAACP and other groups urge the Justice Department to pursue a "civil rights" lawsuit against Zimmerman.
